337
00:33:31,120 --> 00:33:33,641
I can do that right now.

338
00:33:33,641 --> 00:33:36,446
Okay. I'll reheat it for you.

339
00:33:36,446 --> 00:33:40,270
♫ <i>Then please take responsibility</i> ♫

340
00:33:40,270 --> 00:33:48,290
♫ <i>You make me confused about you, I don't want this</i> ♫

341
00:34:36,520 --> 00:34:38,565
Hello, Khun Rena.

342
00:34:38,565 --> 00:34:42,600
I haven't seen you for a while. Will you be staying in Thailand longer this time?

343
00:35:08,749 --> 00:35:12,638
What's wrong? Is the soup not good?

344
00:35:14,024 --> 00:35:15,658
It's not that.

345
00:35:18,769 --> 00:35:21,762
I'm thinking of someone.

346
00:35:22,859 --> 00:35:25,659
She knows me best.

347
00:35:28,905 --> 00:35:32,202
She knows I love corn soup,

348
00:35:35,140 --> 00:35:38,275
so she brought me some every day.

349
00:35:40,630 --> 00:35:44,922
But now she's gone.

350
00:35:48,280 --> 00:35:51,422
I have seldom eaten it again.

351
00:35:54,763 --> 00:35:56,663
Who is she?

352
00:35:58,950 --> 00:36:00,879
My mom.

353
00:36:03,090 --> 00:36:05,589
When I was fifteen,

354
00:36:06,511 --> 00:36:09,009
my mom got remarried.

355
00:36:10,831 --> 00:36:14,068
I haven't eaten it since.

356
00:36:16,530 --> 00:36:20,542
And I had to live alone.

357
00:36:24,203 --> 00:36:26,835
It was hard at first,

358
00:36:27,910 --> 00:36:30,029
but I got through it.

359
00:36:32,450 --> 00:36:38,192
By the way, do you know how to make corn soup?

360
00:36:43,690 --> 00:36:46,429
I think there's a recipe on YouTube.

361
00:36:46,429 --> 00:36:50,149
You know how to make it. That's good.

362
00:36:50,149 --> 00:36:55,010
Then... when I want to eat corn soup,

363
00:36:55,010 --> 00:36:57,520
can you make it for me, Nezumi-san?

364
00:36:58,470 --> 00:37:00,479
Sure.

365
00:37:02,069 --> 00:37:08,095
But now please eat this before it gets cold.

366
00:37:25,110 --> 00:37:27,559
- What?
- It's hot.

367
00:37:27,559 --> 00:37:29,411
I'm sorry.

368
00:37:35,400 --> 00:37:36,923
It's still hot.

369
00:37:36,923 --> 00:37:39,267
I'm sorry. It's still hot.

370
00:37:53,870 --> 00:37:55,679
Boss!

371
00:37:57,470 --> 00:37:59,986
I don't want to eat the soup anymore.

372
00:38:13,349 --> 00:38:15,655
I will get the door for you.

373
00:38:41,055 --> 00:38:43,490
Isn't this Koji's room?

374
00:38:44,580 --> 00:38:47,957
Hey, Koji. How are you?

375
00:38:47,957 --> 00:38:50,229
What are you doing here?

376
00:38:50,229 --> 00:38:52,486
I went to see you at the office.

377
00:38:52,486 --> 00:38:56,342
And they told me you were sick at home so I hurried here.

378
00:38:56,342 --> 00:38:58,763
How are you feeling? Have you taken your medicine?

379
00:38:58,763 --> 00:39:01,562
No. I'm about to.

380
00:39:01,562 --> 00:39:05,779
You're always like this. You don't take care of yourself when I'm not around.

381
00:39:05,779 --> 00:39:09,967
Let me see. Your temperature is quite high.

382
00:39:09,967 --> 00:39:12,178
No one's taken you to the hospital, right? Come on.

383
00:39:12,178 --> 00:39:14,546
- Let's go.
- No, it's okay.

384
00:39:14,546 --> 00:39:17,542
Noom Nim-san bought me some medicine.

385
00:39:17,542 --> 00:39:20,562
This is Noom Nim-san, my secretary.

386
00:39:20,562 --> 00:39:24,760
This is Matsuda Rena, executive director of our parent company.

387
00:39:25,377 --> 00:39:29,863
Hello. Nice to meet you, Khun Rena.

388
00:39:49,156 --> 00:39:52,183
Take off your shirt. I will give you a tepid sponge bath.

389
00:39:52,183 --> 00:39:55,800
There's no need. I'll just take my medicine.

390
00:39:55,800 --> 00:39:58,757
You've never said no before.

391
00:39:59,469 --> 00:40:03,440
Why? Are you feeling uncomfortable because there's someone else here?

392
00:40:22,349 --> 00:40:26,665
You haven't told me what you're doing in Bangkok.

393
00:40:28,020 --> 00:40:32,749
I heard there was an issue because Khun Mark didn't like the brand ambassador.

394
00:40:32,749 --> 00:40:37,539
The problem may have already been fixed, but it's a problem nonetheless.

395
00:40:37,539 --> 00:40:42,505
So I wanted to look into that and audit our company here.

396
00:40:54,268 --> 00:40:59,182
I don't need a hotel room. I'm going to stay at Koji's as usual.

397
00:41:02,199 --> 00:41:05,565
Why aren't you staying at a hotel?

398
00:41:06,319 --> 00:41:08,800
I usually stay here, though.

399
00:41:08,800 --> 00:41:13,190
Besides, I miss you so much.

400
00:41:13,190 --> 00:41:17,240
There are so many things I want to talk with you about in bed.

401
00:41:21,370 --> 00:41:25,169
Please excuse me, I'll be leaving. I have work to do.

402
00:41:25,169 --> 00:41:27,226
Wait. I'll drive you.

403
00:41:28,059 --> 00:41:31,766
It's fine. I can go by myself.

404
00:41:35,799 --> 00:41:37,569
Please excuse me.

405
00:42:12,719 --> 00:42:18,182
Hi, everyone. Many of you might recognize me because I was here last year.

406
00:42:19,120 --> 00:42:22,899
For anyone who's new, I'm Matsuda Rena,

407
00:42:22,899 --> 00:42:26,779
executive director of ViperX's parent company in Japan.

408
00:42:26,779 --> 00:42:30,089
I'm here to audit this company like every year before.

409
00:42:31,969 --> 00:42:38,394
Because of the issues with Khun Mark's case, I'm here to improve the system so it doesn't happen again.

410
00:42:38,394 --> 00:42:41,915
Please take care of me.

411
00:42:43,949 --> 00:42:49,193
All right, the first thing we need to discuss for this year is...

412
00:42:49,193 --> 00:42:52,215
the company's restructuring plan, as decided by the Japan office,

413
00:42:52,215 --> 00:42:55,659
which our subsidiaries have to implement next year.

414
00:43:00,230 --> 00:43:03,288
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

415
00:43:04,509 --> 00:43:06,050
Thank you.

416
00:43:06,050 --> 00:43:07,930
Glad to see you are doing well.

417
00:43:07,930 --> 00:43:11,111
- How are you doing?
- <i>Good</i>

418
00:43:15,243 --> 00:43:16,472
I'm happy.

419
00:43:16,472 --> 00:43:19,937
Great.

420
00:43:19,937 --> 00:43:23,919
<i>- Shall we go out to eat? Come on!
- Sure. Let's go.</i>

421
00:43:23,919 --> 00:43:26,479
<i>Anytime is okay.</i>

422
00:43:28,350 --> 00:43:31,499
<i>- How about sushi?
- Sushi would be fine.</i>

423
00:43:31,499 --> 00:43:35,757
<i>- Or yakiniku (Japanese barbecue)?
- Oh, yakiniku!</i>

424
00:44:13,280 --> 00:44:18,615
Nezumi-san, you will be my secretary again from now on, okay?

425
00:44:20,455 --> 00:44:22,089
Okay.

426
00:44:24,200 --> 00:44:25,830
And also,

427
00:44:25,830 --> 00:44:29,612
please set up a special office for Rena-san.

428
00:44:29,612 --> 00:44:31,522
There's no need.

429
00:44:31,522 --> 00:44:37,409
Don't go through the trouble. I already said that I'll use Koji's office as usual.

430
00:44:37,409 --> 00:44:43,196
I'd also like a cup of coffee, Nezumi-san.

431
00:45:01,493 --> 00:45:05,948
Rena-san is back and beautiful like a model.

432
00:45:05,948 --> 00:45:08,242
<i>That's true.</i>

433
00:45:10,100 --> 00:45:12,709
